{
  "name": "flare",
  "description": "Reference-parity: flare = push-along-(smooth)normals + linear falloff (xfrm.flare). A seg-4 cube is pushed along each vertex's smooth normal (uniform average of incident face normals = the reference engine's default; per-vertex-type face=axis/edge=45deg/corner=diagonal) by dist x linear-weight. Push is linear in weight (v + w*dist*normal). Plain seg cube (no subdivision) keeps topology - hence normals - identical in both engines; a CC mesh leaves a ~0.3deg normal residual from differing subdivision connectivity (documented separately, not a flare bug).",
  "source": "Frozen reference capture (radial falloff, real-GL session; captured from a reference session via the private capture tooling).",
  "provenance": {
    "schema": 1,
    "source": "live-capture",
    "reference": "ref-editor@11.2v3",
    "method": "capture-drag",
    "captured_utc": "unknown",
    "harness": "private capture tooling (generator script outside tools/local/fixture_gen/)",
    "task": null,
